<task id="046" project="sdap-bff-api-remediation-fix">
  <metadata>
    <title>Create `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade interfaces (FR-E1)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 day</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent (developer)</assigned>
    <tags>bff-api, ai-boundary, facade, outcome-e, phase-4</tags>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Must complete before consumer migration tasks 047-050; defines interface signatures</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Create `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` namespace inside `Sprk.Bff.Api`. Define small focused
    facade interfaces (per UQ-07 default): `IBriefingAi`, `IInvoiceAi`, `IRecordMatchingAi`,
    `IWorkspacePrefillAi`, plus any additional interfaces identified by Phase 1's inventory of
    actual consumer usage. Implementations wire to existing `IOpenAiClient` / `IPlaybookService`
    internally. Mirror ADR-007's SpeFileStore pattern (canonical facade-over-Graph-SDK).

    CRITICAL: This task introduces ZERO behavior change — new types only. Compile + test must
    succeed without ANY consumer migration. Tasks 047–050 do the actual migration.

    NOTE: `Services/Ai/Handlers/` already exists (with GenericAnalysisHandler) — `PublicContracts/`
    is a NEW sibling subdirectory.

    **Merge strategy (senior-review G9, owner-binding 2026-05-24)**: Tasks 046–051 are committed individually for per-task POML rigor and review granularity, BUT all 6 commits are bundled into a **single atomic PR** for merge. Rationale: 59-file structural refactor cannot be safely `git revert`ed mid-bake. Squash-merge gives clean atomic rollback if Phase 4 regression appears. See plan.md Process Rules section.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior .NET developer with ADR-007 facade-pattern familiarity.</role>

  <goal>
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` directory exists with:
    - Interfaces: `IBriefingAi.cs`, `IInvoiceAi.cs`, `IRecordMatchingAi.cs`, `IWorkspacePrefillAi.cs` (+ others as discovered)
    - Implementation classes wired to existing AI internals
    - DI registration in appropriate `Add*Module()` extension in Program.cs (without removing existing registrations)

    Build passes. Tests pass within ±5% baseline. ZERO consumer migration in this task.
  </prompt>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
    <file purpose="adr">.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
    <file purpose="canonical-facade">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/SpeFileStore.cs</file>
    <file purpose="existing-ai">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/</file>
    <file purpose="program">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Program.cs</file>
    <file purpose="claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="constraint">.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013 refined">External CRUD consumers MUST go through `Services/Ai/PublicContracts/` facade</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-007">Mirror SpeFileStore facade pattern</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — additional registrations need justification per `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md`</constraint>
    <constraint source=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">Placement Justification required</constraint>
    <constraint source="design.md UQ-07">Small focused interfaces (default), not one large interface</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-007-spefilestore.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-013-ai-architecture.md</file>
